---
title: Patatas Bravas and Crispy Artichokes with a Garlicky Aioli
description: *Patatas bravas* is one of Spain’s most beloved late-night snacks, and we totally understand why. It consists of crispy fried potatoes drizzled with a warm and lightly spiced aioli sauce (are you drooling yet?). You don’t have to be fumbling around the streets of Barcelona in the wee hours to appreciate it, though. We’ve added artichokes, tomatoes, and arugula to give it some veg-focused, dinner-friendly flair.
